<B>Appendix B</B> for information regarding this and other <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-GAAP</FONT> measures. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Most importantly, we
delivered these results while continuing to drive meaningful progress on our path to the Company&#146;s full potential through the execution of our long-term Enterprise Strategy. Early in the pandemic we made the decision to remain fully invested in
our people and in our long-term strategy. The people that we retained and the marketing, innovation and capacity investments that we continued to fund as a result of that decision have the Company very well positioned to continue to accelerate
organic growth, add high-quality <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">bolt-on</FONT> acquisitions, and sustain our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">best-in-class</FONT></FONT> margins and returns in 2022 and beyond. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The quality of ITW&#146;s operations, execution, and financial results throughout the pandemic period demonstrates that ITW is a company that has the enduring
competitive advantages, agility, and resilience necessary to consistently deliver <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">top-tier</FONT> performance in any environment. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>How We Align Executive Compensation with the Enterprise Strategy </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The independent members of our Board of Directors and
Compensation Committee are responsible for aligning executive incentives with the Company&#146;s strategy and the best interests of our stockholders. The Board believes that the Company has a strong track record of thoughtful and diligent governance
and execution with respect to aligning executive incentives, as evidenced by our stockholders&#146; overwhelming support for our annual advisory vote on executive compensation. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">26 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee uses our long-term Enterprise Strategy as a framework to guide our executive compensation
decisions. Our programs are designed to be highly performance-oriented, with rigorous financial goals to reward our executives for <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">best-in-class</FONT></FONT> performance. We
regularly review our annual and long-term incentive plan metrics to ensure ongoing alignment with the strategy&#146;s initiatives and performance objectives. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We
generally link 50&nbsp;percent of our executives&#146; target long-term incentive opportunity to performance awards consisting of share-based units and cash, with three performance goals: three-year average (i)&nbsp;Operating Margin, <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(ii)&nbsp;After-tax</FONT> ROIC, and (iii)&nbsp;EPS growth. The remaining 50&nbsp;percent of our target long-term incentive opportunity consists of stock option awards that only provide compensation value as our stock
price increases. Notably, we do not provide any time-vested full value equity awards (i.e. restricted stock units) to our NEOs. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>ITW&#146;s Focus on Performance-Based Compensation in 2021 </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Variable pay makes up a substantial portion of CEO and NEO compensation, as illustrated in the graphs below. We believe that the mix of incentives in our executive
compensation plans continues to support the achievement of the current phase of our strategy. For 2021, the mix of compensation for our CEO and NEOs was: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

salary, target EIP and the grant date fair value of long-term cash and equity incentives. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The metrics in our annual and long-term incentive plans are designed to

<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" ALIGN="right"> 60&nbsp;<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>ITW <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">5-Year</FONT> CEO Pay Versus Cumulative TSR
Comparison </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Each component of the Company&#146;s compensation structure plays an integral role in motivating our executives to maximize ITW&#146;s
long-term performance potential. As noted above, 92&nbsp;percent of the CEO&#146;s 2021 compensation is variable pay tied to the successful achievement of the Enterprise Strategy&#146;s long-term performance objectives. The following table shows
total CEO pay relative to the Company&#146;s cumulative TSR performance over the last 5 years. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g236440g39u12.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">&nbsp;Notes: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:5%; text-indent:-1%; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">- CEO Pay represents Mr.&nbsp;Santi&#146;s compensation levels based upon his total compensation as reported in the Summary Compensation
Table. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">- Indexed TSR line assumes $100 invested on 12/31/2016 in ITW stock. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_15"></A><A NAME="tx236440_102"></A>Executive Compensation Highlights </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Compensation Philosophy </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="92%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="33%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="65%"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt" BGCOLOR="#00416a">
<TD HEIGHT="5" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="5" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#00416a" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" NOWRAP STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Philosophy</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Key Components</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" ROWSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our executive compensation philosophy is designed to deliver competitive total compensation upon the achievement of our strategy objectives, which will attract, motivate
and retain leaders who drive the creation of long-term stockholder value.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-right:0.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Target total compensation is based on the median of our peer group and other relevant external market data. Actual compensation is determined by
achievement of results based on our goals aligned with ITW&#146;s strategy.</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Individual executive compensation is
then established based on an executive&#146;s scope of responsibility, impact on profitable growth, individual performance and breadth of experience.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> through short- and long-term incentives links
compensation to Company and business segment performance. This <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;pay-at-risk&#148;</FONT></FONT> aligns executive interests with those of our stockholders to help ensure the
short- and long-term growth of ITW.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>

</DIV></Center>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Compensation Objectives </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We emphasize a total compensation approach in establishing individual executive compensation levels with each component of compensation serving a specific purpose. In
addition to paying a competitive base salary, we use a mix of different performance-based components of compensation that reward different aspects of Company, business segment, and individual performance. Our 2021 executive compensation program
consisted of both fixed (base salary) and variable (annual cash incentives and long-term incentive compensation) components, as illustrated below: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>2021 Compensation Components </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Ongoing Best Practices </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We regularly review and refine our executive compensation programs to ensure that they continue to address practices and policies that are aligned with our <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> philosophy and the interests of our stockholders. In this regard, our 2021 compensation program reflects the following: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="99%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="46%"></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#00416a" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT
 COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">What We Do</FONT></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #ffffff; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT
 COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">What We Don&#146;t Do</FONT></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Pay for Performance</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I></I></B>Our NEOs&#146; average total target compensation is 84% performance based.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.40em; text-indent:-2.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Employment Agreements
</I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We do not provide executive officers with employment agreements.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.40em; text-indent:-2.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Robust Stock Ownership Guidelines</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have stock ownership guidelines for our executive officers of 6 x salary for CEO, 3 x salary for Vice Chairman, Executive Vice Presidents and CFO
and 2 x salary for Senior Vice Presidents. Executives must retain the net after tax shares of vested or exercised awards if guidelines are not met within five years.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Tax <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Gross-ups</FONT> </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We do not provide tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-ups</FONT> as part of our <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> agreements.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Annual &#147;Say on Pay&#148; Vote</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We hold an annual advisory vote for our stockholders to review and approve our executive compensation programs.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Repricing </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We do not allow share repricing within our stock option plan.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Independent Compensation Consultant</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I></I></B>The Committee: (1)&nbsp;engages an independent compensation consultant who advises the Committee on regulatory and other current
trends and key developments in executive compensation and (2)&nbsp;reassesses its consultant&#146;s independence annually.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Hedging/Pledging of Company
Equity Securities</I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We prohibit executive officers and directors from engaging in any transaction that is designed to hedge or offset a
decrease in the market value of ITW common stock and from pledging ITW equity securities.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Annual CEO and NEO Performance Review</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I></I></B>The Committee conducts an annual review of the performance of the CEO, as well as the other executive officers.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Dividends on Unvested Equity
Awards </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Dividends accrued on unvested equity awards, including restricted stock units and performance share units, are not paid unless
awards vest.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Annual Review of Compensation Programs</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I></I></B>The Committee, with input from its independent compensation consultant, conducts an annual review of our executive compensation
programs, considering business strategies, best practices and good governance.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Single-Trigger <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Change-In-Control</FONT></FONT> Vesting/Benefits</I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We do not allow immediate
vesting of equity awards that are continued or replaced upon a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control;</FONT></FONT> all such awards allow only double-trigger vesting <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(change-in-</FONT></FONT><BR>control and termination).</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Clawback Policy</I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I></I></B>Our Compensation Recovery Policy provides for the reimbursement of incentives if a material financial restatement is required, whether
or not based on misconduct, and equity forfeiture provisions for violations of restrictive covenants and certain misconduct related to restatement.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="2" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD>
<TD HEIGHT="2" COLSPAN="2"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#00416a"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman; " COLOR="#00416a">&#10003;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Annual Compensation Risk Assessment </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Each year we perform an assessment of risks that could result from our executive compensation practices.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">30 </P>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Say on Pay Advisory Voting Results </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2019, 2020 and 2021, 95.9&nbsp;percent, 95.0&nbsp;percent, and 93.9&nbsp;percent, respectively, of votes cast approved the compensation of our NEOs. The Committee
believes these favorable votes confirm the pay of our NEOs is appropriately aligned with the performance of the Company and the interests of our stockholders. The Committee therefore determined that it was not necessary to make any changes to our
executive compensation practices during 2021 as a result of the Say on Pay votes. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_16"></A><A NAME="tx236440_103"></A>How We Make Compensation Decisions </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Role of the Compensation Committee </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
Committee conducts an annual review of ITW&#146;s practices and the compensation of our executive officers to ensure: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">The components of the total compensation package are aligned with the market to attract and retain the caliber of talent
required to deliver on our business strategies; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Compensation decisions are appropriately differentiated to reflect the contributions of our highest performers; and
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Our incentive plans drive performance aligned with our strategy and the Company&#146;s culture and values.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In making its executive compensation decisions and recommendations, the Committee is guided by the following factors: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Our compensation philosophy; </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Compensation comparisons from a peer group of diversified multinational industrial companies with similar size, value, and
complexity; and </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Our executive&#146;s contribution to our short- and long-term goals based on profitable growth and strong returns on
capital. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">See &#147;Board of Directors and its Committees&#151;Compensation Committee&#148; under &#147;Proposal&nbsp;1&#151;Election&nbsp;of
Directors&#148; for more information about the function of the Committee. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Role of the Compensation Consultant </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee engaged Frederic W. Cook&nbsp;&amp; Co., Inc. (&#147;Cook&#148;) until May 2021 and Meridian Compensation Partners LLC (&#147;Meridian&#148;) beginning in
June 2021, both of whom are independent advisors. The Committee&#146;s advisors work directly on its behalf and in cooperation with management to review ITW&#146;s executive compensation programs, confirm appropriateness of our peer companies, and
assess our compensation governance process. In 2021, Meridian conducted a marketplace review of the compensation we pay to our executive officers. Meridian provided the Committee with relevant market data, including a review of our pay and
performance and that of our peers, reviewed the peer companies we use for comparison purposes, and benchmarked our compensation against our peer companies. Meridian also assisted the Committee with its assessment of compensation-related risk. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">With respect to CEO compensation, on an annual basis, the Company&#146;s independent compensation consultant provides an independent recommendation to the Committee for
its consideration. In developing its recommendation, the consultants rely on their understanding of ITW&#146;s business, strategy and compensation programs, as well as their own independent research and analysis including ITW&#146;s peer group. The
consultants do not meet with the CEO with respect to his compensation. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">31 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Peer Companies </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="48%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee has identified a group of comparable companies, which we refer to as the peer group, to benchmark executive compensation and provide
competitive market data to be used in establishing and recommending each component of compensation. The peer group is reviewed annually by the Committee with assistance from its independent compensation consultant.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2021, the Committee utilized market data for compensation benchmarking from a custom survey
consisting of the peers below, as provided by Aon plc, a global provider of compensation data.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In connection with its annual review in 2021, the Committee determined that no changes to the peer group were warranted.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-TOP:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-RIGHT:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00pt solid #00416a; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:8pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Peer&nbsp;Group&nbsp;Selection&nbsp;Criteria:</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;U.S. publicly traded companies from ITW&#146;s same and related industries, identified based on
Standard&nbsp;&amp; Poor&#146;s Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS) codes;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Companies with <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-fourth</FONT> to four times our revenue and
market capitalization with broadly similar businesses and pay models;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Companies that compete for the same customers with similar products and/or services; and</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&#8194;&#8201;&#8202;Companies with whom we may
compete for executive talent.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The revenue median of the peer group was $17.1&nbsp;billion based on the twelve-month average of reported financial results through
June&nbsp;15, 2021, and the median market capitalization was $48.2&nbsp;billion, versus $12.9&nbsp;billion and $73.3&nbsp;billion, respectively, for ITW. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The nature
of our decentralized and diverse lines of business presents challenges in identifying similar organizations for comparison purposes; however, we believe that the selected peer group provides relevant comparisons. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Compensation Decisions and Individual Compensation Levels </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On an annual basis, the CEO reviews the total compensation of the NEOs and makes recommendations to the Committee based on his assessment of each executive&#146;s
individual performance and peer group compensation information. The Committee makes recommendations to the independent directors regarding the CEO&#146;s compensation based on an assessment of the CEO&#146;s performance and peer group compensation
information. There are no material differences in the policies and decision processes used in setting compensation for the CEO and the other NEOs. However, the different levels of compensation for the NEOs, as shown in the Summary Compensation Table
of this proxy statement, reflect internal factors such as each executive&#146;s scope of responsibility, performance, impact on profitable growth and breadth of experience, as well as compensation data from the peer group. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">32 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_17"></A><A NAME="tx236440_104"></A>Components of the 2021 Executive
Compensation Program </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I><A NAME="tx236440_105"></A>Base Salary </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In
determining base salary, the CEO and the Committee consider the size and scope of the executive officers&#146; responsibilities, experience, performance, market data and the median base salary of similar positions at our peer group companies. The
Committee believes that median base salary is an appropriate general reference point to use for encouraging solid performance. Base salaries are reviewed annually, and adjustments are intended to recognize performance and contributions over the
prior year, as well as any significant changes in duties or scope of responsibility. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For 2021, the Committee recommended no base salary increase for Mr.&nbsp;Santi,
which was approved by the Board&#146;s independent directors. For the other NEOs, the Committee approved recommended base pay merit increases ranging from 4 to 5&nbsp;percent. These base salary increases were effective February&nbsp;22, 2021. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I><A NAME="tx236440_106"></A>Annual Executive Incentive Plan </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that executives generally should be rewarded for their contributions to the overall financial success measured by income and organic growth of the Company as
a whole, and, if applicable, the business segment he or she leads. Achieving our annual financial objectives is important to executing on our current strategic objectives and delivering long-term value to stockholders. The Committee determines and
approves the performance results and awards for the NEOs and recommends the CEO&#146;s annual incentive award amount for approval by the independent directors of the full Board. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company provides annual incentive award opportunities to the NEOs through the annual Executive Incentive Plan (EIP). The Committee determined each NEO&#146;s 2021
award target based on responsibilities, experience, performance, market data and the median target incentive opportunity of similar positions at our peer group companies. Based on achieved results against performance goals, an NEO may earn between
zero percent and 200% of his or her award target. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For 2021, the Committee approved the following performance metrics and weightings: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">For Messrs. Santi, O&#146;Herlihy, Larsen, and Ms.&nbsp;Lawler, the performance metrics were the Company&#146;s operating
income (weighted 60 percent) and organic revenue growth (weighted 40 percent). </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">For Mr.&nbsp;Hartnett, the performance metrics were operating income (weighted 60 percent) and organic revenue growth
(weighted 40 percent), with 50&nbsp;percent of each metric based on Company results and 50&nbsp;percent on results of his business segment. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
financial measures were recommended by management and approved by the Committee at the start of the performance year. While the Committee has the discretion to make adjustments in the calculation of financial performance to eliminate factors beyond
the control of management and to eliminate possible disincentives to act in the long-term best interests of the Company, the Committee made no adjustments to the EIP payouts in 2021. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">33 </P>

</DIV></Center>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>

<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I><A NAME="tx236440_107"></A>Long-Term Incentives </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="61%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="38%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-right:0.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The value of the overall long-term incentive award for the CEO is determined by the Committee, subject to approval by the
independent directors of the full Board of Directors. Awards to the other NEOs are recommended by&nbsp;the CEO to the Committee for approval.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-right:0.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The key factors in determining the awards are the executive&#146;s position, performance, potential to contribute to the long-term success of the
Company, breadth of experience, and prior awards. In addition, although we generally do not establish any specific target or prescribed value in relation to the peer group, comparisons are made to long-term incentive levels in the peer group and
market compensation data.</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-TOP:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-RIGHT:2.00pt solid #00416a; BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00pt solid #00416a; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Long-term Incentive Philosophy</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that ensuring the long-term growth and profitability of the business is a primary management responsibility. Therefore, a significant portion of an executive
officer&#146;s compensation should be directly linked to key financial performance measures that consider the long-term perspective, such as operating margin, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">After-tax</FONT> ROIC, EPS and ITW&#146;s share price
over time.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2021, the value of the NEOs&#146; long-term incentive awards consisted of approximately 44&nbsp;percent in the form of stock options
and 56&nbsp;percent in the form of PSUs and Performance Cash awards. We believe that stock options are an effective incentive because they directly align the interest of the executives with those of our stockholders. Similarly, we believe PSUs and
Performance Cash awards are effective because they incent executive leaders to achieve key long-term financial goals. Stock options are combined with performance-based awards to closely align the realized value of long-term incentives with the
financial performance objectives of the Company&#146;s strategy and total shareholder return. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee increased the value of PSUs for the 2021-2023
performance cycle (in the range of 14 to 15&nbsp;percent of the overall LTI opportunity for each NEO) in recognition of their strong performance successfully managing the Company through the unprecedented operational challenges created by the global
pandemic during 2020. Importantly, management decided not to initiate any enterprise-wide employment reductions during 2020 in furtherance of its commitment to protect the health and well-being of employees. As a result of the Committee&#146;s
decision, the long-term incentive award mix for 2021 is weighted slightly more towards PSUs than in prior years. The adjustments to the weightings of long-term incentive award types in 2021 remain closely aligned to ITW&#146;s <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> philosophy. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee has established specific vesting and
expiration provisions associated with termination of employment due to death, disability and retirement, as defined in the applicable awards, and forfeiture provisions upon other termination of employment. The Committee, in its sole discretion, may
deem a long-term incentive award, whether vested or unvested, to be immediately forfeited if the recipient competes with the Company, engages in gross misconduct or conduct that is against the business interests of the Company, or divulges
confidential information about the Company to others. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B>2021 Stock Option Awards </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The 2021 stock options vest in equal installments over a four-year period ending in 2025. Stock options are awarded with an exercise price equal to the fair market value
of the common stock on the date of grant and normally expire ten years after the award date. The Committee awards <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified</FONT> stock options because it believes that the tax benefits to the Company from <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified</FONT> stock options outweigh the potential tax benefits to the NEOs from incentive stock options. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B>2021-2023 Performance Share Units and Performance Cash Awards </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The PSUs and Performance Cash awards vest three years from the date of grant, subject to the achievement of the performance goals set at the beginning of the performance
period. PSUs are </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">35 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
awarded based on the fair market value of one share of ITW common stock on the date of the award. Dividend equivalents are accrued and added in the form of units to the original PSU awards as
reinvested dividends. These reinvested dividends are paid only on PSUs earned at the end of the performance period. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The goals for the 2021 PSUs and Performance Cash
awards are equally weighted and based on three-year average operating margin, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">After-tax</FONT> ROIC and EPS growth. The payout range is 50&nbsp;percent to 200&nbsp;percent of the target award for threshold to maximum
performance. Performance below threshold results in no payout for the weighted portion for that metric. The payout at the end of the performance period will be based on the following payout scale: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B>2019-2021 Performance Share Units and Performance Cash Awards Payout </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2019, executives were awarded PSUs and Performance Cash awards with a three-year performance period from January&nbsp;1, 2019 to December&nbsp;31, 2021. The awards
had the same financial metrics (operating margin, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">After-tax</FONT> ROIC, and EPS growth) and weightings as the 2021-2023 performance awards noted above. Consistent with last year&#146;s practice and ITW&#146;s <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> philosophy, the Committee determined not to exercise its discretion to increase the payouts of those 2019-2021 awards beyond achievement of the <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pre-established</FONT> payout targets despite the unforeseeable impact of the COVID pandemic and its impact on 2020 financial performance. The table below details the performance and associated payouts of the 2019-2021 PSU
and Performance Cash awards: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

(1/3rd)</P></TD>
