<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">1.8%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">(14.3)%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">28.4%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">5.3%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">5.0%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">8.0%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">12.0%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">55.0%</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><B>Total Payout % of Target:&nbsp;107.5%&nbsp;</B> </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B>Timing of Long-Term Incentive Awards </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
Committee meets in February of each year following the Company&#146;s public release of its earnings results for the most recently completed fiscal year to review and approve long-term incentive awards for the executive officers. Long-term awards
are made in compliance with the Long-Term Incentive Plan, including the requirement that stock options may not be awarded at less than 100&nbsp;percent of the fair market value of ITW&#146;s common stock on the date of grant. The exercise price of
the awards is based on the closing price of ITW&#146;s stock on the date of award. We do not time award grant dates for the purpose of enhancing the value of executive compensation. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">36 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_18"></A><A NAME="tx236440_108"></A>Compensation Governance Practices and
Policies </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Stock Ownership Guidelines </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe
that stock ownership is important because it aligns the interests of our management and directors with those of our stockholders and mitigates compensation-related risk. Because of the importance of stock ownership, the Board of Directors and the
Committee have adopted stock ownership guidelines for executive officers and directors. The guidelines for stock ownership as a multiple of executive officers&#146; base salaries and of directors&#146; annual cash retainers are as follows: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="99%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="3%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#00416a" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #ffffff; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Title</FONT></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT
 COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Guideline</FONT></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt" align="left">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chief Executive
Officer</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">6 times salary</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Vice Chairman, Executive Vice Presidents, and Chief Financial
Officer</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">3 times salary</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Senior Vice
Presidents</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">2 times salary</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> Directors</P> <P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">5 times annual cash retainer</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:1pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If the applicable ownership guideline is not met within a five-year time period, the covered executive officer or <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director must retain 100% of the net <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">after-tax</FONT> shares received from the vesting or any subsequent exercise of awards until the ownership guidelines are met. The
achievement of these guidelines is reviewed annually. The Board of Directors believes that its stock ownership guidelines are appropriate, reasonable and attainable given the responsibilities and compensation levels of our executive officers and
directors. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All executive officers and directors who have been in their positions for five or more years have met or exceeded the applicable stock ownership
guidelines. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Hedging and Anti-Pledging Policy </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Pursuant to the Company&#146;s Hedging/Anti-Pledging Policy, all employees (including executive officers) and directors who receive equity-based awards from the Company
are prohibited from trading ITW options or engaging in short sales of ITW stock. In addition, all executive officers and directors and their designees are prohibited from purchasing or selling any financial instrument or otherwise engaging in any
transaction that hedges or offsets, or is designed to hedge or offset, any decrease in the market value of ITW equity securities. In addition, since April 2013, our executive officers and directors have been prohibited from pledging ITW stock, and
all pledged shares are excluded from ownership for purposes of our stock ownership guidelines. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Compensation Recovery Policy
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We maintain a Compensation Recovery Policy (clawback policy) applicable to all executive officers of the Company subject to Section&nbsp;16 of the
Securities Exchange Act of 1934. Under the policy, the Committee will seek reimbursement of incentives paid to executive officers in the prior three years where the payment was predicated upon the achievement of certain financial results with
respect to the applicable performance period that was subsequently the subject of a material restatement due to <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-compliance</FONT> of the Company with any financial reporting requirement under the U.S. securities
laws. The reimbursement amount would be imposed whether or not the restatement is based on misconduct. The amount recovered would be measured by the excess of the gross incentive payment made over the gross payment that would have otherwise been
made if the original payment had been determined based on the restated financial results. Further, following a material restatement of our financial statements, we will seek reimbursement of compensation and profits from trading in Company stock
received by our CEO and CFO to the extent required under Section&nbsp;304 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">37 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, forfeiture provisions in the terms of awards under our equity incentive plan provide flexibility to
cancel outstanding grants for violation of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-compete</FONT> and confidentiality restrictive covenants, and for engaging in gross misconduct or conduct that is against the business interests of the Company
regardless of whether a financial restatement is required. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>2021 Risk Assessment </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee, together with management and Meridian, annually considers potential risks when reviewing our compensation programs for all employees, including our
executive officers. Based on this assessment, the Committee concluded that our 2021 compensation programs do not create risks that are reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on ITW. In making this determination, the Committee reviewed
the key design elements of our compensation programs, as well as the means by which any potential risks may be mitigated, including: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">A Balanced Mix of Compensation Components &#151; The target compensation mix for our executive officers is composed of base
salary, annual cash incentives and long-term cash and equity incentives, representing a mix that is not overly weighted toward short-term cash incentives. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Multiple Performance Factors &#151; Our incentive compensation plans use Company-wide measures, which encourage focus on
the achievement of objectives for the overall benefit of the Company. Multiple financial goals also prevent an overemphasis on any one metric. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Long-Term Incentives &#151; Our long-term incentives are primarily equity-based, and our PSUs and Performance Cash awards
are subject to performance goals. These long-term incentives have three-year vesting schedules (PSUs and Performance Cash) or four-year vesting schedules (stock options), in each case to complement our annual cash-based incentives.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Capped Incentive Awards &#151; Annual and long-term incentive awards, PSUs and Performance Cash are all capped at
200&nbsp;percent of target. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Stock Ownership Guidelines &#151; Our guidelines call for significant share ownership, which further aligns the interests
of our executive officers and directors with the long-term interests of our stockholders. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Clawback Policy &#151; Our Compensation Recovery Policy authorizes the Committee to recoup past incentive compensation in
the event of a material restatement of the Company&#146;s financial results, whether or not based on misconduct. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Prohibition on Hedging and Pledging &#151; Executive officers and directors are subject to Company policy that prohibits
hedging and pledging activities with respect to ITW stock. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Committee Oversight &#151; The Committee has ultimate authority to determine, and reduce if appropriate, compensation
provided to our executive officers.</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Independent Compensation Consultant &#151; The Committee retains an outside independent compensation consultant.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Committee&#146;s Independent Consultant </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Meridian, the independent compensation consultant, has been retained by and reports directly to the Committee. It also provides peer group directors&#146; compensation
data to the Corporate Governance and Nominating Committee; it does not have any other consulting engagements with management or ITW. Based on its consideration of factors under NYSE listing standards, the Committee concluded that the work performed
by Meridian and its senior advisor involved in the engagement did not raise any conflict of interest or independence concerns. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">38 </P>

</DIV></Center>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:14pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_19"></A>NEO Compensation </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_20"></A><A NAME="tx236440_109"></A>Summary Compensation Table </B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following tables provide information regarding the compensation of our NEOs. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">These amounts include an amount of interest in the applicable calendar year considered to be in excess of market rates
credited to the deferred compensation accounts of the NEOs under the ECRIP, discussed in more detail under &#147;Nonqualified Deferred Compensation&#148; below. When a participant attains retirement eligibility at age 55 with 10 years of service,
any amounts in his or her ECRIP account deferred prior to January&nbsp;1, 2010 are entitled to a return of 130&nbsp;percent of the monthly Moody&#146;s Corporate Bond Yield Average rate, and the excess interest portion is deemed to be amounts
exceeding 100&nbsp;percent of such rate. This additional interest credit applies to all eligible plan participants, including the eligible NEOs. All amounts deferred after December&nbsp;31, 2009 accrue interest at 100&nbsp;percent of the
Moody&#146;s Rate. The individual amounts of pension benefits and excess interest credits earned in each year are shown in the table below. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>

exceptions for termination upon death, disability, retirement and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control.</FONT></FONT> </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">PSUs were granted in 2019, 2020, and 2021 and are subject to three-year vesting, as well as achievement of operating
margin, <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">After-tax</FONT> ROIC and EPS performance goals. The number of PSUs included in this table assumes target performance is met. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_23"></A><A NAME="tx236440_112"></A>Option Exercises and Stock Vested
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following table provides information
regarding option exercises and stock vesting for each NEO during 2021. The value realized upon the exercise of options is calculated using the difference between the option exercise price and the market price of ITW&#146;s common stock at the time
of exercise multiplied by the number of shares underlying the option. The value realized upon the vesting of stock awards is based on the closing price of ITW&#146;s common stock on the vesting date. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="84%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>

<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD style="width:100pt"></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD></TD>
<TD style="width:100pt"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD style="width:62pt"></TD>
<TD></TD>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Assuming the individual receives a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">lump-sum</FONT> distribution at normal retirement,
present values are based on the 2.73&nbsp;percent discount rate used for financial reporting purposes. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(2)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">In the event of a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> or
departure due to death, disability or retirement, the total pension payable is reflected in the total of the above amounts. The allocation between the ITW Retirement Accumulation Plan and the ITW Nonqualified Pension Plan depends on the actual lump
sum and annuity values calculated using the actual applicable interest rates and Internal Revenue Service (IRS) limits. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Mr.&nbsp;Larsen, who joined the Company in September 2013, is not eligible for the Company&#146;s pension plans, as the
plans were closed to employees hired after January&nbsp;1, 2007. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD WIDTH="8%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Herlihy participated in the ITW Retirement Accumulation Plan from 1989 through 1999. From 1999 through
August 2011, he was employed in Ireland, participated in the ITW Irish Pension Plan and ceased active participation in the U.S. plan. Upon his return to the U.S. in 2011, he ceased active participation in the Irish plan and was ineligible to
actively participate in the U.S. plan due to the plan participation closure effective January&nbsp;1, 2007. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Ms.&nbsp;Lawler, who joined the Company in October 2014, is not eligible for the Company&#146;s pension plans, as the
plans were closed to employees hired after January&nbsp;1, 2007. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_25"></A><A NAME="tx236440_114"></A>ITW Retirement Plans </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>ITW Retirement Accumulation Plan </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We
maintain the ITW Retirement Accumulation Plan (the Pension Plan) for the benefit of eligible employees to provide a portion of the income necessary for retirement. The Pension Plan was closed to new entrants effective January&nbsp;1, 2007. The
Pension Plan is structured as a &#147;pension equity plan&#148; under which a participant accumulates an <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">age-based</FONT> percentage for each year of plan participation. The sum of the Accumulation Percentages
multiplied by final average annual pay (salary and annual incentive EIP paid in the highest five years out of the last ten complete calendar years of service), plus the sum of the Excess Percentages multiplied by the final average annual pay above
the Covered Compensation, produce an amount that can be received as a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">lump-sum</FONT> payment or an actuarially equivalent lifetime annuity. For each year of credited service after December&nbsp;31, 2000, the <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">age-based</FONT> percentages are as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="99%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">Covered Compensation is a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">35-year</FONT> average of the maximum earnings recognized in
calculating Social Security benefits. For 2021, the Covered Compensation amount for an individual attaining age 65 was $94,560, while for an employee age 35 or younger it was $142,368. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Prior to 2001, the Pension Plan operated under a traditional annuity formula (a normal retirement benefit equal to 1&nbsp;percent of final average annual pay and
0.65&nbsp;percent of such pay in excess of covered compensation for each of the first 30 years of credited service plus 0.75&nbsp;percent of final average annual pay for any additional years). As part of the transition to the pension equity formula,
as of December&nbsp;31, 2000: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="11%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Accrued benefits under the traditional annuity formula were converted to an initial pension equity percentage by
calculating the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">lump-sum</FONT> value of the normal retirement annuity and dividing by the average annual pay at that time. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">Participants who had 5 years of participation and whose age plus vesting service equaled at least 50 years were entitled to
additional pension equity credits of 4&nbsp;percent of final average annual pay per year for each year of employment from 2001 through 2015. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">44 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>ITW Irish Pension Plan </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Irish Pension Plan operates under a traditional annuity formula (a normal retirement benefit equal to 1.5&nbsp;percent of final average annual pay for each year of
credited service). The final average annual pay is the highest consecutive pensionable base salary over any three-year period over the last ten complete years of service. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Nonqualified Pension Plan </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
Nonqualified Pension Plan is maintained to make up for benefits that cannot be paid under the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">tax-qualified</FONT> Pension Plan due to Internal Revenue Code limitations on the amount of compensation that may be
considered and the amount of benefit that may be paid. The Company has not considered awarding additional years of service to executive officers under the plan and, therefore, does not currently have a policy on such awards. For the most part, the
Nonqualified Pension Plan uses the same formulas and other computation elements as the Pension Plan with certain exceptions, including the following: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="11%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">The Pension Plan uses net compensation after deferrals under the Executive Contributory Retirement Income Plan (ECRIP), and
the Nonqualified Pension Plan uses total eligible compensation (generally, salary and EIP award). </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="11%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">The Nonqualified Pension Plan provides that a participant who leaves the Company, other than upon retirement, may forfeit
any plan benefits based on eligible compensation above the IRS maximum amount ($290,000 in 2021) that may be recognized under a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">tax-qualified</FONT> plan. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="11%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">In addition to the annuity and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">lump-sum</FONT> options available under the Pension Plan, a
participant in the Nonqualified Pension Plan may elect to receive fixed monthly installments over 2 to 20 years. If the executive left employment prior to death, disability or retirement, or if the plan is terminated in conjunction with a <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control,</FONT></FONT> the benefit from the Nonqualified Pension Plan would be paid as a lump sum. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Nonqualified Deferred Compensation </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
Company&#146;s ECRIP offers designated executives an opportunity to defer a portion of their salary and earned <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-equity</FONT> incentive to a deferred compensation account to receive the Company contributions they
would otherwise receive if such deferrals had been made under our <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">tax-qualified</FONT> Savings and Investment Plan and IRS limits did not apply. Deferred amounts receive a rate of interest based on the monthly
Moody&#146;s Long-Term Corporate Bond Yield Average (Moody&#146;s Rate). All the NEOs are eligible for the ECRIP. An ECRIP participant may defer from 6&nbsp;percent to 50&nbsp;percent of his or her salary and from 6&nbsp;percent to 85&nbsp;percent
of his or her variable cash components (EIP and Performance Cash), with the applicable Company matching contribution on the salary and EIP amounts under the Savings and Investment Plan formula (in lieu of any matching contributions under that plan).
Salary and EIP deferrals under the ECRIP reduce the compensation that may be recognized under the Savings and Investment Plan and the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">tax-qualified</FONT> Pension Plan. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For employees who are not eligible to participate in the pension plan due to the participation freeze on January&nbsp;1, 2007, the Company contributes a <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-elective</FONT> contribution to the Savings and Investment Plan, up to the IRS Compensation Limits and continues to contribute above the IRS Compensation Limits to this plan. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">45 </P>

</DIV></Center>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">5.0%</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">10.0%</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8">
<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; line-height:14pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL">At least 70</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">6.0%</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8">
<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:14pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">11.7%</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(1)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left">For 2021, the Social Security Wage Base was $142,800. </P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The ECRIP features include a maximum limit on the amount of interest under the Moody&#146;s Rate that would be recognized (12&nbsp;percent annualized, or
15.6&nbsp;percent for amounts eligible to receive 130&nbsp;percent of the Moody&#146;s Rate), a return of deferral feature whereby an individual could elect to receive a return of the principal amount deferred after a period of at least five years,
and options for payment following death, disability or retirement as a lump sum or in monthly installments over 2 to 20&nbsp;years. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Retirement under the ECRIP is
defined as having attained age 55 with at least 10 years of service, or age 65 with at least 5 years of service. If an ECRIP participant&#146;s employment ends due to retirement, death, or disability, amounts deferred to the ECRIP prior to
January&nbsp;1, 2010 will receive interest crediting of 130&nbsp;percent of the Moody&#146;s Rate. Amounts deferred to the ECRIP after December&nbsp;31, 2009 are only eligible to receive 100&nbsp;percent of the Moody&#146;s Rate. During 2021, the
Moody&#146;s Rate applied to ECRIP accounts ranged from 2.80&nbsp;percent to 3.21&nbsp;percent for amounts eligible for 100&nbsp;percent of the Moody&#146;s Rate, and 3.64&nbsp;percent to 4.18&nbsp;percent for amounts eligible for 130&nbsp;percent
of Moody&#146;s. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If terminated in conjunction with a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control,</FONT></FONT> participants
would receive their ECRIP as <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">a&nbsp;lump-sum</FONT> payment. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following table sets forth ECRIP account information for each NEO
during fiscal year 2021. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:8.5pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">$346,371</P></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:8.5pt; font-family:ARIAL">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">
<P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; line-height:12pt; font-size:8.5pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mary K Lawler*</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:8.5pt; font-family:ARIAL">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:8.5pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right">-&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:8.5pt; font-family:ARIAL">&nbsp;</P></TD>

<TD NOWRAP VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-size:8.5pt; font-family:ARIAL">&nbsp;</P></TD>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; text-indent:3%; font-size:6.5pt; font-family:ARIAL">* Ms.&nbsp;Lawler was not an NEO in 2020 and 2019. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_26"></A><A NAME="tx236440_115"></A>Potential Payments upon Termination </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:2pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our severance and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> protections are designed to be fair and competitive.
These protections are intended to retain executives in the event they need to consider actions that may impact job security or ease an executive&#146;s transition at retirement. These benefits help us compete for talent and are fully within the
range of competitive practice at similar companies. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Further, our NEOs are not covered by employment agreements and are employed &#147;at will.&#148; No payments or
benefits are automatically payable to NEOs upon a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control,</FONT></FONT> and if there is a qualifying termination following a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control,</FONT></FONT> there are no tax <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">gross-up</FONT> payments. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">47 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Payments and benefits received by NEOs upon termination are governed by the arrangements described below and
quantified at the end of this section. We have estimated the amounts involved assuming that the termination became effective as of December&nbsp;31, 2021. The actual amounts to be paid out can only be determined at the time of the NEOs&#146;
departure from the Company. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Annual Executive Incentive Plan </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The EIP provides that if a participant is employed as of the last day of the fiscal year, he or she would receive any amounts earned under the EIP for that fiscal year.
In the event an NEO becomes permanently disabled or dies, the NEO would be eligible for a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pro-rated</FONT> payout under the EIP. If termination of employment other than for death, disability, retirement or <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> occurs prior to the last day of the fiscal year, a participant forfeits his or her award; however, the Compensation Committee has the discretion to award an
amount prorated for the portion of the fiscal year that the participant was employed. Actual amounts earned by the NEOs based on performance in 2021 are discussed in more detail above in &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis &#151; Components
of the 2021 Executive Compensation Program &#151; Annual Executive Incentive Plan.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>ITW Retirement Accumulation Plan and
Nonqualified Pension Plan </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">NEOs who are terminated for any reason receive their benefits under the ITW Retirement Accumulation Plan and Nonqualified
Pension Plan as described in the Pension Benefits tables above. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Executive Contributory Retirement Income Plan </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">NEOs who are terminated for any reason receive contributions and accumulated earnings as outlined in the Nonqualified Deferred Compensation section above. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I>Long-Term Incentive Plan Awards </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Stock
Options</I>: In the event of a termination upon death or disability, all unvested options held by the NEOs would immediately vest. In the event of a termination upon retirement (defined as a combined age and service of 70, subject to a minimum age
of 55 and a minimum service of 5 years), 75&nbsp;percent of stock options granted within one year from the retirement date would be forfeited and the remaining would continue to vest. Additionally, stock options granted more than one year from the
retirement date would continue to fully vest. Messrs. Santi, O&#146;Herlihy, and Hartnett meet the retirement criteria for the 2019, 2020 and 2021 awards as of December&nbsp;31, 2021. In the event of a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control,</FONT></FONT> stock options that are not continued or replaced would fully vest and those that are continued or replaced would only vest upon involuntary termination of employment after the <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control.</FONT></FONT> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>PSUs and Performance Cash</I>: In the event of a termination upon
death or disability, the awards would vest based on the actual performance level achieved and be paid after the end of the performance period. In the event of a termination upon retirement (defined as a combined age and service of 70, subject to a
minimum age of 55 and a minimum service of 5 years), the awards would vest <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pro-rata</FONT> based on date of termination and be paid after the end of the performance period. In the event of a <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control,</FONT></FONT> an award that is not continued or replaced will fully vest on the date of the
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> at the greater of target or actual achievement level and payment will be pro rata based on the number of days during the applicable performance period
before the occurrence of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control.</FONT></FONT> In the event of involuntary termination of employment within two years following a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control,</FONT></FONT> an award that has been replaced would fully vest without conditions. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For all NEOs, in the event of a
termination other than upon retirement, death, disability or a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control,</FONT></FONT> any unvested options, PSUs, and Performance Cash held on such date by the NEOs would be
forfeited. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">48 </P>

</DIV></Center>


<p style="margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:0em; page-break-before:always">
<HR SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<Center><DIV STYLE="width:8.5in" align="left">

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><I><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Change-in-Control</FONT></FONT> Severance Policy </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company&#146;s 2011 <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Change-in-Control</FONT></FONT> Severance Compensation Policy provides that,
upon an actual or constructive termination following a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> of the Company, the NEOs and other elected officers would be entitled to receive: (i)&nbsp;two
times annual cash compensation (base salary plus average annual incentive pay over the prior three years); (ii) a prorated amount of that year&#146;s annual incentive bonus at the target level (or actual achievement level if greater); and
(iii)&nbsp;a prorated amount of the value of Performance Cash awards at the target level (or actual achievement level if greater). Notwithstanding the foregoing, if the payments under the preceding clauses (ii)&nbsp;and (iii) were not replaced at
the time of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control,</FONT></FONT> then such awards will be deemed to be earned and immediately payable at the greater of target or actual achievement level pro rata
based on the number of days during the applicable performance period before the occurrence of the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control.</FONT></FONT> We do not gross up any of the compensation paid in
the event of termination due to a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control.</FONT></FONT> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_27">
</A><A NAME="tx236440_116"></A>Summary of Termination and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Change-in-Control</FONT></FONT> Provisions </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The benefits for the NEOs under each termination scenario are outlined below. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

is not achieved, the award is forfeited. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> do not receive accelerated vesting. Double-trigger vesting occurs for awards that are continued or replaced if actual or constructive termination
occurs within two years of a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> of the Company. </P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL; " ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Pro-rata</FONT> amount is at the greater of target or actual achievement level.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_28"></A><A NAME="tx236440_117"></A>Termination and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Change-in-Control</FONT></FONT> Payments and Benefits </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following table shows the value of payments and benefits
that the NEOs would receive pursuant to the 2011 Long-Term Incentive Plan, the 2015 Long-Term Incentive Plan and the 2011 <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Change-in-Control</FONT></FONT> Severance Compensation Policy
upon retirement, involuntary termination without cause, death, disability or a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control,</FONT></FONT> assuming that termination occurred as of the last business day of
fiscal 2021. It also shows the Company&#146;s severance benefits that would be payable to the NEOs and that are available to employees generally. For purposes of this table, Performance Cash and PSU payments are assumed at target level. The value of
unvested stock options, if accelerated upon a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> or termination, is&nbsp;determined using the excess, if any, of $246.80 (the closing price of ITW common
stock on December&nbsp;31, 2021) over the option exercise price. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Messrs.&nbsp;Santi, O&#146;Herlihy, and Hartnett met the retirement criteria for various grants
under the Long-Term Incentive Plan during 2021. In case of retirement, the 2019, 2020, and 2021 PSUs and Performance Cash awards would vest and be payable after the performance goals have been met. The unvested stock options continue to vest. In
addition, 75&nbsp;percent of the 2021 stock option awards would be forfeited since the assumed retirement would have occurred within one year from the grant date. The PSUs and Performance Cash awards would be
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pro-rated</FONT> based on the retirement date. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Voluntary termination without good reason is not shown in the table because such a
termination would not trigger the payment of severance benefits or accelerated vesting of long-term awards. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Stock options, PSUs and Performance Cash awards, whether
vested or unvested, are subject to forfeiture if the holder competes with, or divulges confidential information about, the Company, or if the Compensation Committee determines that the holder engaged in gross misconduct or conduct that is against
the business interests of the Company. Awards are also subject to forfeiture, in whole or in part, to comply with applicable law, regulation, stock exchange rules, accounting rules, or our clawback policy. </P>

<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Compensation Committee of the Board of Directors hereby
furnishes the following report to the stockholders of the Company in accordance with rules adopted by the Securities and Exchange Commission. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have reviewed and
discussed with management the Compensation Discussion and Analysis contained in this proxy statement. Based on our review and discussions, we have recommended to the Board of Directors that the Compensation Discussion and Analysis be included in
this proxy statement and the Company&#146;s Form <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2021. </P>

<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following table provides information as of

<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Plan Category</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE=" BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">(a)</FONT></B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">to&nbsp;be issued upon<BR>exercise&nbsp;of&nbsp;outstanding<BR>options, warrants and</FONT></B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#00416a"><B><A NAME="rom236440_31"></A>Pay Ratio </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #00416a">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As required by Section&nbsp;953(b) of the Dodd-Frank Wall
Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act, and Item 402(u) of Regulation <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">S-K,</FONT> we are providing the following information about the ratio of the annual total compensation of the median ITW employee to the
annual total compensation of our CEO. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The pay ratio reported below, in our view, is a reasonable estimate calculated in a manner consistent with SEC rules, and is
based on the methodologies and assumptions described below. SEC rules identifying the median employee and determining the pay ratio permit companies to employ a wide range of methodologies, estimates and assumptions. As a result, the pay ratio
reported by other companies, which may have utilized other permitted methodologies or assumptions, and which may have a significantly different workforce structure from ours, are likely not comparable to our CEO pay ratio. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Company has an extensive global footprint in 52 countries and approximately 45,000 employees as of December&nbsp;31, 2021, of which approximately <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">two-thirds</FONT> are outside of the U.S. While compensation and benefits practices in these countries vary considerably, we provide market competitive compensation and benefits, maintain fair labor practices and ensure
work environments that reflect our core values and culture everywhere we operate. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To calculate the pay ratio, we identified the median employee based on our
employee population as of October&nbsp;31, 2020, which was approximately 43,000 employees, before excluding approximately 2,000 employees by applying the exemption noted below. As permitted by the SEC, we have maintained the same median employee we
identified in 2020 to calculate the 2021 pay ratio. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In many countries, ITW has small employee populations. In 2020, we chose to apply the SEC&#146;s de minimis
exemption and excluded countries which, in the aggregate, make up under 5% of our total workforce. The countries excluded are as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="99%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">
